latestPosts.caption:
This beauty was one of our first Sculpt and Balance patients while we were determining the exact methodology to the treatment. She looks beautiful, soft, feminine, and contoured. 

All filler treatments require upkeep, they last approximately 2 years where you have visible and happy results. We advise patients have one small refresh of filler every 12-18 months and we touch up areas that are slowly fading away. This is how we ensure natural and continuous improvement in your Sculpt and Balance investment as you age 🩷🩷

latestPosts.caption:
The Sculpt and Balance ™️ This patient’s stunning full-face transformation/facial reshaping involved advanced techniques with filler and neuromodulator. Her after photos are seamless, feminine, contoured … but still natural and undetectable. Thank you to this beauty for being a patient of mine for almost 8 years and trusting me with her injection journey. This result was created slowly and carefully. 

To learn more about if you’re a candidate for our Sculpt and Balance ™️, send me a DM saying Sculpt and Balance, and we can offer you a free in person or virtual consultation 🖤

We don’t do puffy or over-done. We always measure to create the precise narrowing, widening, or elongating effects our patients are looking to achieve, while always optimizing for beautiful and natural results. This beautiful patient had neuromodulators in her jawline to slim the lateral (back) portion of her lower face, while using a thick but fluid hyaluronic acid filler in the medial (front) portion of her lower face.

Thank you for your trust ❤️
